  "texts": [
    "They often inserted additional vowels into consonant clusters, turning words like \"strength\" into \"sterength.\"",
    "English learners of Azerbaijani, on the other hand, frequently violated vowel harmony and struggled with velar fricatives.",
    "Both groups exhibited errors in intonation, with learners applying the intonation patterns of their native language to their second language.",
    "The phonetic differences between Azerbaijani and English significantly contribute to the common pronunciation difficulties faced by learners of both languages.",
    "These difficulties primarily stem from the complex vowel system in English compared to the more straightforward system in Azerbaijani, as well as the differences in consonant inventory, consonant clusters, and intonation patterns."
